                                "slug": "mechanical-administration",
                                "titleText": "Existing Mechanical Systems",
                                "children": [
                                    {
                                        "ancestorRefs": [
                                            "12",
                                            "M1202"
                                        ],
                                        "body": "<span class=\"u-italic\">Additions</span>, <span class=\"u-italic\">alterations</span>, renovations or repairs to a <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> shall conform to the <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/4/foundations#R401.2\">requirements</a> for a new <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> without requiring the existing <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> to comply with all of the <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/4/foundations#R401.2\">requirements</a> of this code. <span class=\"u-italic\">Additions, <span class=\"u-italic\">alterations</span></span> or repairs shall not cause an existing <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> to become unsafe, hazardous or overloaded. Minor <span class=\"u-italic\">additions</span>, <span class=\"u-italic\">alterations</span> or repairs to existing <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical systems</a> shall meet the provisions for new <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/5/floors#R504.1.2\">construction</a>, unless such work is done in the same manner and arrangement as was in the existing system, is not hazardous, and is <span class=\"u-italic\">approved</span>.",
                                        "depth": 2,
                                        "diagrams": [],
                                        "displayRef": null,
                                        "displayTitle": "M1202.1 Additions, Alterations or Repairs",
                                        "hasAssemblies": false,
                                        "isContiguous": true,
                                        "numAssembliesOnRef": 0,
                                        "numBuildingProductsOnRef": 0,
                                        "numDiagramsOnRef": 0,
                                        "reference": "M1202.1",
                                        "slug": "mechanical-administration",
                                        "titleText": "Additions, Alterations or Repairs",
                                        "children": []
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "ancestorRefs": [
                                            "12",
                                            "M1202"
                                        ],
                                        "body": "Except as otherwise provided for in this code, a provision in this code shall not require the removal, <span class=\"u-italic\">alteration</span> or abandonment of, nor prevent the continued use and maintenance of, an existing <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> lawfully in existence at the time of the adoption of this code.",
                                        "depth": 2,
                                        "diagrams": [],
                                        "displayRef": null,
                                        "displayTitle": "M1202.2 Existing Installations",
                                        "hasAssemblies": false,
                                        "isContiguous": true,
                                        "numAssembliesOnRef": 0,
                                        "numBuildingProductsOnRef": 0,
                                        "numDiagramsOnRef": 0,
                                        "reference": "M1202.2",
                                        "slug": "mechanical-administration",
                                        "titleText": "Existing Installations",
                                        "children": []
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "ancestorRefs": [
                                            "12",
                                            "M1202"
                                        ],
                                        "body": "<a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">Mechanical systems</a>, both existing and new, and parts thereof shall be maintained in proper operating condition in accordance with the original design and in a safe and sanitary condition. Devices or safeguards that are required by this code shall be maintained in compliance with the code edition under which such devices and safeguards were installed. The <span class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#owner\">owner</a></span> or the <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#owner\">owner</a>'s designated agent shall be responsible for maintenance of the <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical systems</a>. To determine compliance with this provision, the <span class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#building_official\">building official</a></span> shall have the authority to require a <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/washington/wa-residential-code-2021/chapter/2/definitions#mechanical_system\">mechanical system</a> to be reinspected.",
                                        "depth": 2,
